  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine the myeongnan-roe, Greek yogurt, fermented red pepper paste, olive oil, garlic, cumin, and salt. Mix until smooth.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a greased 9x9 inch baking dish.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes or until the edges are golden brown.",
    "Remove from the oven and sprinkle with parsley.",
    "Let it rest for 5 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!",
    "Be careful as the fermented bake will be very hot when removed from the oven.",
    "Let it cool down completely before refrigerating or freezing for later use."
